perusing the printed page events at stanford perusing the printed page facebook twitter email print add to calendar this half day program highlights the book exhibitions on view this summer at the cantor arts center and the stanford libraries betsy fryberger the center's curator emerita of prints drawings and photographs discusses her exhibition illustrated title pages 1500 1900 in conjunction with the exhibition the art of the book in california carolee campbell from the ninja press talks about the field of fine press artists books gail wight stanford professor of art and art history describes her classroom project turned gallery display the fusion of art and science the program includes information about this summer's typography exhibition at the stanford libraries when saturday july 30 2011 1 00 pm approximate duration of 3 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags lecture reading arts contact 723 4177 admission open wed sun 11am 5pm thursdays until 8pm admission is free closed monday and tuesday permalink http events stanford edu events 271 27149 more info last modified july 15 2011
